+      spanReceiverHost.closeReceivers();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should spanReceiverHost be assigned null at the end of the if block ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13540945" author="mbertozzi" created="Sat, 29 Dec 2012 17:46:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;spanReceiverHost is private and only the master uses that, so I&apos;d say no need to assign to null since is not exposed and we&apos;re in the shutdown phase. (not that also the others assignmentManager, serverManager &amp;amp; co are not assigned to null after shutdown)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13540946" author="jmhsieh" created="Sat, 29 Dec 2012 17:48:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The other managers are not forced to null, so it seems ok to keep it this way.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
